sql:
SELECT code_smells.type
FROM code_smells
WHERE code_smells.class = 'GuiManager' AND code_smells.project_id = 0;

external_knowledge:
Project 1 refers to a specific project in the database where code smells were detected and resolved; 
A code smell is any symptom in the source code of a program that possibly indicates a deeper problem; 
A user who resolves code smells is someone who has fixed issues in the project's code.

sql:
SELECT COUNT(user_id) 
FROM project_users 
WHERE project_id = 1;

SELECT cs.project_id, COUNT(cs.smell_id) AS num_smells, AVG(cs.severity) AS avg_severity
FROM code_smells cs
GROUP BY cs.project_id;

SELECT severity, COUNT(smell_id) AS smell_count
FROM code_smells
GROUP BY severity;

SELECT COUNT(smell_id) 
FROM code_smells 
WHERE project_id = 0;

SELECT smell_history.*
FROM smell_history
WHERE smell_history.smell_id = 1;

SELECT cs.*
FROM code_smells AS cs
JOIN projects AS p ON cs.project_id = p.project_id
JOIN project_users AS pu ON p.project_id = pu.project_id
WHERE pu.user_id = (
    SELECT user_id FROM users WHERE username = 'john_doe'
) AND cs.project_id IN (
    SELECT ar.project_id FROM analysis_results AS ar
    WHERE ar.smell_count > 0
);

SELECT project_id, COUNT(DISTINCT user_id) AS unique_contributors
FROM project_users
GROUP BY project_id;

external_knowledge:
- 'Fixed' status implies the code smell has been resolved; 
- 'resolved_by' = 0 indicates the code smell was resolved by a specific user, possibly the one who reported it or the project lead; 
- 'project_id' = 1 refers to a specific project for which the code smells are being analyzed.

sql:
SELECT type, description 
FROM code_smells 
WHERE project_id = 1;

SELECT h.project_id, COUNT(DISTINCT h.resolved_by) AS num_users
FROM smell_history h
GROUP BY h.project_id;
